### 2.1 Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Language | Python 3.12 (requires ≥3.11) | Virtual env at `.venv/` |
| UI | PySide6 (Qt6) | LGPL licensed |
| Video | OpenCV (cv2) | All major codecs via FFmpeg backend |
| Arrays | NumPy | Image data as `(H, W, 3)` uint8 |
| Image I/O | Pillow (PIL) | PNG/TIFF read/write |
| 3D Preview | PyVistaQt + VTK | Qt-embedded 3D viewer |
| 3D Export | trimesh + pygltflib | OBJ (manual), glTF/GLB (trimesh) |
| PDF | ReportLab | Printable unfold PDFs |
| Packaging | PyInstaller | Not yet configured |

### 2.2 Design Patterns

- **MVC**: Models (`models/`), Views (`ui/`), Controllers (`processing/`)
- **QThread Workers**: All processors extend `BaseProcessor(QThread)`. UI thread never blocks.
- **Signal-Slot**: Qt signals for progress, completion, errors between threads and UI
- **Strategy Pattern**: Each mode has its own processor class with a common `BaseProcessor` interface
- **Central State**: `ProjectState(QObject)` holds all settings; UI panels read/write it directly

### 2.3 Memory & Performance

| Strategy | Implementation |
|----------|---------------|
| Streaming | `VideoSource.get_frame_range()` reads sequentially via `cap.read()` loop — never loads full video |
| Edge-only (void) | ~18KB/frame vs ~6MB. Only edge pixels stored for cuboid/cylinder void |
| Sampling rate | User-configurable Nth frame skip. Reduces processing proportionally |
| Preview after export | 3D preview builds ONLY after files are written to disk |
| Texture cap | Preview textures capped at 2048×2048 (`PREVIEW_TEXTURE_MAX`) |
| Disk-based fill | Cuboid Fill writes each frame to disk as PNG (not RAM) |
| Memory warning | Warns user if estimated usage > 1GB (`MEMORY_WARN_THRESHOLD_MB`) |

