### 3.5 Generate Pipeline (MainWindow._on_generate)

1. Validate: video loaded, valid frame range, mode-specific checks (cuboid mask ≥10×10)
2. Memory warning if estimated > 1GB
3. Get output dir from ExportControls (auto-creates subfolder: `{video}_{mode}_{timestamp}/`)
4. Instantiate processor:
   - "Slice" → `SliceProcessor(state, output_dir)` (handles orthogonal internally)
   - "Cuboid" → `CuboidVoidProcessor` or `CuboidFillProcessor` based on `cuboid_fill_mode`
   - "Cylinder" → `CylinderProcessor(state, output_dir)`
   - "Rings" → `RingsProcessor(state, output_dir)`
5. Disable all controls, start processor via `generate_panel.start_with_processor(processor)`
6. On finish → export mesh (if 3D mode) → show preview → re-enable controls

