**REMARKS**: Implemented with disk-based strip storage (`.npy` files in `_strips_tmp/`) to avoid RAM saturation on long videos — similar architecture to CuboidFillProcessor. DrawingCanvas is a QObject data model (not a widget overlay); drawing interaction is handled directly in FrameViewer's mouse events for consistency with other modes. Line width ≥ 2 uses perpendicular band expansion based on local tangent. 3D preview displays each drawn line as a textured "curtain" mesh (2D surface following the path in XY, extending along Z/time) inside a wireframe cuboid representing the video volume. Long lines are subsampled to max ~500 mesh segments for preview performance. Slit-Tear mode auto-assigned to mode_controls_stack index 2. Ctrl+Z undo handled via SlitTearControls signal → DrawingCanvas.undo().

