### Step 3.3: Object Extraction (Edge Detection + AI Segmentation)
**Status**: [x] DONE — 2026-04-17
**Estimated complexity**: Very High

**Objective**: Extract object silhouettes from each frame for the filled cuboid, enabling "figure trails" through time. Two extraction backends: classical edge detection (zero dependencies) and U²-Net AI segmentation (ONNX Runtime). Both support fully automatic and point-prompt (click-to-select) modes.

**What was built** — `processing/object_detector.py`:

- **Edge Detection** (`extract_edge_mask`): Canny + morphological closing + contour filling. Params: canny_low, canny_high, dilate_iter, min_area. Auto mode keeps all contours above min_area; point-prompt keeps only the contour containing the clicked point.
- **AI Segmentation** (`extract_ai_mask`): U²-Net salient object detection via ONNX Runtime. Model cached at `~/.cache/deep-vid-visualizer/models/`. Two models: u2netp (4.7 MB, fast) and u2net (176 MB, quality). Auto mode thresholds the probability map; point-prompt keeps only the connected component at the clicked point.
- **Unified API** (`extract_mask`): Dispatches to the correct backend based on `mode` parameter.
- **`apply_extraction_mask`**: Applies binary mask to RGB image → RGBA output.
- **Model download**: `download_model(model_name, progress_callback)` downloads from GitHub to cache dir.
- ONNX session is lazy-loaded and cached globally. Supports CUDA, CoreML, DirectML, and CPU providers.

**What was built** — UI in `ui/sidebar/cuboid_controls.py`:

- Fill Mode dropdown now enabled: "Void (edges only)" / "Fill (all pixels)"
- Extraction group (visible only in Fill mode) with Method dropdown: None / Chroma Key / Edge Detect / AI Segment
